- The main nodejs program runs on a single thread (Event loop)
- Nodejs program : Queues
  - Timers queue : stores all the callbacks of setTimeout and setInterval methods that need to be executed on the event loop
  - IO callbacks queue: stores all the callbacks of completed IO operations(by the libuv threads) that now need to be executed on the event loop
  - Promises callback queue: stores all the .then and .catch callbacks of the Promises object